{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PxfQJ1CsP5W9xUmvLGwQ88","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The logs reveal the root issue: \n\n1. The HTTP server is bound to `127.0.0.1:8080` (localhost only) on `crdb-cluster-1`, while on other pods it's `0.0.0.0:8080`.\n2. This means the readiness probe (which hits `http://:http/health?ready=1`) can't reach the HTTP server on the pod, causing it to fail.\n\nFrom the pod spec:\n```\nif [ \"$POD_NAME\" = \"crdb-cluster-1\" ]; then\n  HTTP_ADDR=\"127.0.0.1:8080\";\nelse\n  HTTP_ADDR=\"0.0.0.0:8080\";\nfi\n```\n\nSo the HTTP address for `crdb-cluster-1` is bound to localhost only, which means the kubelet's probe can't reach it from outside the container, causing the readiness probe to fail with \"connection refused\". There are also connection errors between nodes with DNS lookup failures and TCP timeouts on port 26257, plus a potential NetworkPolicy blocking that port.\n\nNow I need to examine the StatefulSet spec and any NetworkPolicies to understand the full picture. The core issue is that the startup command intentionally binds the HTTP server to 127.0.0.1 only for the first pod, which prevents external readiness probes from connecting. The fix would be to patch the StatefulSet to remove this condition so all pods listen on 0.0.0.0:8080.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6100,"cache_read_input_tokens":29370,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6100},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d08f3a8c-2677-4e9f-9382-093333eb4e61","uuid":"258ce8cf-da60-43f4-8128-cccecf5f7c99","request_id":"req_011Ccc1DR5XLhyKbHTnqNBf1"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PxfQJ1CsP5W9xUmvLGwQ88","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The key issue is clear from the logs: `crdb-cluster-1` binds its HTTP server to `127.0.0.1:8080` (localhost only), so the Kubernetes readiness probe can't reach it from outside the container. The StatefulSet command has an intentional condition causing this. Let me inspect the full spec and NetworkPolicies."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6100,"cache_read_input_tokens":29370,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6100},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d08f3a8c-2677-4e9f-9382-093333eb4e61","uuid":"c884146e-db1a-479e-815f-a8b291e840a6","request_id":"req_011Ccc1DR5XLhyKbHTnqNBf1"}
