{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018JvfzyffqHtf7puwLk6Nbc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see two problems:\n\n1. **StatefulSet command bug**: The command binds `crdb-cluster-1`'s HTTP server to `127.0.0.1:8080` instead of `0.0.0.0:8080`, making health probes fail.\n\n2. **NetworkPolicy `block-crdb-sql`**: The NetworkPolicy only allows ingress on port 8080, but crucially it has **no source selector**. This means:\n   - Only port 8080 (HTTP) is allowed\n   - Port 26257 (SQL/GRPC) is blocked, which explains why the nodes can't communicate with each other on that port for gossip and inter-node connections\n   - The NetworkPolicy only allows ingress on port 8080, implicitly blocking everything else\n\nI need to fix two things: update the StatefulSet command to use the correct HTTP address for all pods, and modify the NetworkPolicy to allow port 26257 for inter-node communication. I should tackle the NetworkPolicy first so the nodes can talk to each other, then restart the StatefulSet so pod-1 picks up the corrected configuration. Delete the NetworkPolicy since it's blocking port 26257, which CockroachDB needs for inter-node communication and replication. Then patch the StatefulSet to remove the conditional HTTP binding logic so all pods consistently expose the HTTP interface on 0.0.0.0:8080, which will trigger a rolling restart to apply the fix. So crdb-cluster-1 is running the problematic revision with the bad HTTP binding condition. When I patch the StatefulSet to fix the command and always bind to `0.0.0.0:8080`, it'll trigger a rolling update that restarts crdb-cluster-1 with the corrected configuration. I need to delete the `block-crdb-sql` NetworkPolicy and then patch the StatefulSet using kubectl.\n\nWriting the patch command...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3221,"cache_read_input_tokens":35470,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3221},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d08f3a8c-2677-4e9f-9382-093333eb4e61","uuid":"63d2c956-1b55-41d5-b6fe-6ffbce7c52cf","request_id":"req_011Ccc1EYpt9s3A3PWACqsHK"}
